<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-03-10T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-03-10T16:00:00-05:00" n="743" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d743">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">863.51 Relief Credits/52: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Austria</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Washburn</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-03-10T16:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">March 10,
                                        1928—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>17. Department’s 16, your 12.<note n="36" xml:id="d743fn36"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_882">pp. 882</ref> and
                                    <ref target="#pg_885">885</ref>.</note> Please informally
                            mention to appropriate official [the] general nature of report contained
                            in London Embassy’s telegram 46, March 9, 4 p.m., repeated to Vienna,
                            and telegraph further comment as soon as possible.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>